•  $(x, y, z) = (\texttt{"a"}, \texttt{"a"}, \texttt{"a"})$;
•  $(x, y, z) = (\texttt{"a"}, \texttt{"aa"}, \texttt{""})$;
•  $(x, y, z) = (\texttt{"aa"}, \texttt{"a"}, \texttt{""})$.
In the third test case, there are $8$ valid triples:
